			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I don't think this is a good idea after all.  After a breakpoint, we can easily modify all registers (e.g. to enable single-stepping), but the code path for starting a thread doesn't support modifying all registers.

Also, we want breakpoint support in the debug stub anyway (issue 2983), and having an extra initial breakpoint does not add much complexity.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-09-05T21:42:17.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-09-05T21:42:17.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 2 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2939#c2" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2939/comments/full/2" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>